cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new technique for distributed learning using machine learning algorithms and deep neural networks.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on distributed learning and proposes a new synchronous parallel protocol for networked nodes to collaborate and update model parameters.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses iterative algorithms used in machine learning and proposes a new technique to improve their convergence speed and scalability.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a new technique for deep neural network algorithms to improve their performance in distributed learning.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the design of a distributed learning framework and its impact on the performance and scalability of the system.
